00:05:34.728 --> 00:05:37.920
For the phrases Immortality of the Soul,

00:05:37.920 --> 00:05:40.950
and Domestic Dogs do not
often find themselves

00:05:40.950 --> 00:05:43.540
in the same academic journals.

00:05:43.540 --> 00:05:45.420
Indeed, the study of immortal soul

00:05:45.420 --> 00:05:46.759
and the study of dogs

00:05:46.759 --> 00:05:51.380
seem on first pass not to
bear on one another at all.

00:05:51.380 --> 00:05:53.130
But, of course, there's
plenty of precedent

00:05:53.130 --> 00:05:56.300
for discussing the possibility
of the immortal souls

00:05:56.300 --> 00:05:58.780
of dogs or of any animal.

00:05:58.780 --> 00:06:00.570
There's been furious debate on the topic,

00:06:00.570 --> 00:06:04.010
although the fury has been
stretched out over centuries.

00:06:04.010 --> 00:06:08.970
In Ancient Egypt, dogs and
souls were intertwined.

00:06:08.970 --> 00:06:13.230
Depictions of Anubis, this
dog-headed jackal or other canid,

00:06:13.230 --> 00:06:17.060
often decorated tombs, as a
guide of deceased human souls

00:06:17.060 --> 00:06:18.493
into the immortal realm.

00:06:19.520 --> 00:06:22.200
Meso American cultures
repeated this motif,

00:06:22.200 --> 00:06:25.290
leaving pottery figures of
dogs within burial sites

00:06:25.290 --> 00:06:28.253
as chaperones of human
spirits to the underworld.

00:06:29.120 --> 00:06:30.320
But was the dog himself

00:06:30.320 --> 00:06:33.290
a traveler to that selfsame underworld?

00:06:33.290 --> 00:06:34.313
Surely not.

00:06:35.410 --> 00:06:37.986
In Ancient Greece against
the backdrop of Plato's

00:06:37.986 --> 00:06:41.840
reasoning, immortal soul,
the Aristotelian take

00:06:41.840 --> 00:06:44.577
on the soul was more
generous, implicating,

00:06:44.577 --> 00:06:48.820
"that which can sense
and move" as ensouled.

00:06:48.820 --> 00:06:50.273
Certainly dogs were included.

00:06:51.540 --> 00:06:54.510
So, also would have been
single celled organisms

00:06:54.510 --> 00:06:58.743
like paramecium, which flexibly
react to their environments,

00:06:59.730 --> 00:07:03.890
or, the Mimosa pudica, a sensitive plant,

00:07:03.890 --> 00:07:06.570
which responds in real
time to being touched

00:07:06.570 --> 00:07:08.993
as here from top to bottom.

00:07:09.860 --> 00:07:13.183
Immortality, for plant or
dog, is another question.

00:07:14.530 --> 00:07:16.370
More recently, and most prominently,

00:07:16.370 --> 00:07:18.520
from the vantage of contemporary science

00:07:18.520 --> 00:07:21.960
was DeCartes dualism,
segregating human animals

00:07:21.960 --> 00:07:24.200
from non-human animals with the claim that

00:07:24.200 --> 00:07:26.310
only humans have a soul not liable

00:07:26.310 --> 00:07:28.783
to die with the body, thus, immortal.

00:07:29.720 --> 00:07:33.449
To animals he granted
souls but a material soul,

00:07:33.449 --> 00:07:35.900
so intertwixed with body that it would die

00:07:35.900 --> 00:07:37.840
when the body dies.

00:07:37.840 --> 00:07:40.960
Of course the extension of DeCartes' claim

00:07:40.960 --> 00:07:43.490
that the immortal soul
was restricted to humans

00:07:43.490 --> 00:07:46.070
was that the mortal soul of animals

00:07:46.070 --> 00:07:50.010
was shortly interpreted to
be no sort of soul at all.

00:07:50.010 --> 00:07:52.390
Quite rapidly, one
transitions from this posture

00:07:52.390 --> 00:07:55.510
to reducing animals to simple machinery,

00:07:55.510 --> 00:07:57.983
thus, incapable of
feelings including pain.

00:07:58.820 --> 00:08:01.770
Animals were hence subjected
to incredibly brutal treatment

00:08:01.770 --> 00:08:03.520
under the guise of this philosophy.

00:08:05.050 --> 00:08:08.070
Today, by contrast, that
many current pet owners

00:08:08.070 --> 00:08:10.840
believe in the availability
of the afterlife for animals

00:08:10.840 --> 00:08:13.480
is implied by a phenomenon Stanley Brandes

00:08:13.480 --> 00:08:15.900
has recently drawn our attention to again,

00:08:15.900 --> 00:08:20.322
the development and
success of pet cemeteries.

00:08:20.322 --> 00:08:21.155
(audience laughs)

00:08:21.155 --> 00:08:23.570
Such as New York's Heartsdale Pet Cemetery

00:08:23.570 --> 00:08:26.920
and Paris' CimetiÃ¨re des Chiens.

00:08:26.920 --> 00:08:30.481
Each features inscribed
monuments on the grave sites,

00:08:30.481 --> 00:08:33.917
formal burials and pastoral services.

00:08:33.917 --> 00:08:37.500
Surely, those who have
buried their animals thusly

00:08:37.500 --> 00:08:40.010
are moved to do so by the at minimum,

00:08:40.010 --> 00:08:41.950
their sense of the continued importance

00:08:41.950 --> 00:08:44.123
of the animal's fate after death.

00:08:45.311 --> 00:08:48.093
And often, as when a monument reads,

00:08:48.093 --> 00:08:52.310
"Our friend forever", or "See you later",

00:08:52.310 --> 00:08:55.413
their anticipation that they
will, indeed, see them later.

00:08:56.930 --> 00:08:59.370
We are thus confronted
with a range of opinions

00:08:59.370 --> 00:09:00.470
on the matter at hand.

00:09:01.730 --> 00:09:05.190
The insistence that animals
have immortal souls,

00:09:05.190 --> 00:09:08.330
that animals have souls,
but not immortal ones,

00:09:08.330 --> 00:09:12.130
and that animals have neither
souls nor are they immortal.

00:09:12.130 --> 00:09:14.220
If you're keeping track, that leaves us

00:09:14.220 --> 00:09:18.059
one option undiscussed,
and it will be my tack,

00:09:18.059 --> 00:09:20.280
to suggest that the
question of soul is not

00:09:20.280 --> 00:09:23.923
an answerable one, but that
indeed, dogs are immortal.

00:09:25.970 --> 00:09:28.240
To clarify, I want to
suggest that the question of

00:09:28.240 --> 00:09:29.580
the soulfulness of the animal

00:09:29.580 --> 00:09:32.110
is not the question we should be asking.

00:09:32.110 --> 00:09:33.300
To be sure, there's precedent

00:09:33.300 --> 00:09:35.193
for asking questions of this sort.

00:09:36.050 --> 00:09:40.010
For example, much current
research in non human animals

00:09:40.010 --> 00:09:41.630
comes from comparative psychology,

00:09:41.630 --> 00:09:44.580
which asks questions
cast in a similar mold.

00:09:44.580 --> 00:09:48.170
Have any animals the
intelligence of humans?

00:09:48.170 --> 00:09:51.500
Do they feel the emotions that we do?

00:09:51.500 --> 00:09:54.740
Answers are discoverable, why,
yes, they perform admirably

00:09:54.740 --> 00:09:57.670
like humans on this
test of problem solving,

00:09:57.670 --> 00:10:01.940
or, no, they do not succeed
at being quite human,

00:10:01.940 --> 00:10:04.083
at this task of social cognition.

00:10:05.050 --> 00:10:09.270
But, with comparison to humans,
or, to what humans value

00:10:09.270 --> 00:10:12.820
as our measure, this approach
patently circumscribes

00:10:12.820 --> 00:10:15.680
what we are able to see
in non-human animals.

00:10:15.680 --> 00:10:18.190
It delimits the abilities
they have to those

00:10:18.190 --> 00:10:21.710
which mirror ours, curbs our imagination

00:10:21.710 --> 00:10:24.420
from extending outside our humanness.

00:10:24.420 --> 00:10:27.023
The investigation ends
before it even gets going.

00:10:27.930 --> 00:10:31.150
It is reminiscent of the
famed exercise in exploration

00:10:31.150 --> 00:10:33.030
and knowledge gathering
that might be called

00:10:33.030 --> 00:10:35.410
The Safari Phenomenon.

00:10:35.410 --> 00:10:38.220
Gone to seek animals,
the patient observer,

00:10:38.220 --> 00:10:40.850
looking our over a
savannah, will finally see

00:10:40.850 --> 00:10:45.270
a majestic creature approaching,
then another, then a herd.

00:10:45.270 --> 00:10:48.020
We tend to ask "What is that?"

00:10:48.020 --> 00:10:53.020
It's identification, a greater
kudu, is met with head nods,

00:10:53.260 --> 00:10:55.613
and aborts most further inquiry.

00:10:56.580 --> 00:10:59.840
We move on, no closer to understanding

00:10:59.840 --> 00:11:02.440
the creatures we have
spotted, they have been named.

00:11:03.580 --> 00:11:06.530
Similarly, designation of
the chimp as "like humans"

00:11:06.530 --> 00:11:09.770
in these ways, or the rock
dove as most "unlike humans"

00:11:09.770 --> 00:11:12.610
in these other ways brings us no closer

00:11:12.610 --> 00:11:14.573
to understanding chimp nor dove.

00:11:15.620 --> 00:11:18.440
I think the aim of scientific
inquiry into animals

00:11:18.440 --> 00:11:21.280
should be by contrast, animal centered,

00:11:21.280 --> 00:11:23.773
unpacking what their actual experience is.

00:11:24.620 --> 00:11:26.920
The question then, of the soul of the dog,

00:11:26.920 --> 00:11:29.160
strikes me as an illustrative example

00:11:29.160 --> 00:11:31.623
of asking the wrong question of the dog.

00:11:32.560 --> 00:11:35.540
Having established or determined,
or living in the hope,

00:11:35.540 --> 00:11:38.260
that we have immortal souls ourselves,

00:11:38.260 --> 00:11:41.976
we turn to the pup at our
feet and wonder it at them.

00:11:41.976 --> 00:11:44.860
I do not mean by calling
this the wrong question

00:11:44.860 --> 00:11:46.510
that that question is not germane

00:11:47.461 --> 00:11:48.813
because the dog has no soul.

00:11:49.680 --> 00:11:51.470
Instead, it's not relevant to the dog

00:11:51.470 --> 00:11:53.050
because of his dogness.

00:11:54.490 --> 00:11:57.500
In the first part, the
lion's share, as it were,

00:11:57.500 --> 00:11:59.600
of my lecture, I'll
expand upon this point,

00:11:59.600 --> 00:12:03.210
and try to say something
about what dogness amounts to,

00:12:03.210 --> 00:12:05.253
and just how and why we've missed it.

00:12:06.530 --> 00:12:08.730
Following that, I will
suggest, putting aside

00:12:08.730 --> 00:12:11.270
the question of the dog's soulful status,

00:12:11.270 --> 00:12:13.443
that the dog is in many ways, immortal.

00:12:14.330 --> 00:12:17.020
For the concern with
immortality is transparently

00:12:17.020 --> 00:12:21.230
the interest in persistence,
that our essence,

00:12:21.230 --> 00:12:24.700
that those things we value, engage in,

00:12:24.700 --> 00:12:27.200
or that we define ourselves
through our interactions with,

00:12:27.200 --> 00:12:30.583
can live on in some sense
after we or they die.

00:12:31.600 --> 00:12:32.810
In the final part of this lecture,

00:12:32.810 --> 00:12:35.200
I'll describe how dogs
have attained immortality

00:12:35.200 --> 00:12:37.800
through the roles they play or have played

00:12:37.800 --> 00:12:40.300
in our perception of them
in contemporary society.

00:12:42.360 --> 00:12:44.790
I will begin, though, with a claim,

00:12:44.790 --> 00:12:49.130
as it has some currency these
days, that dogs have souls.

00:12:49.130 --> 00:12:51.223
What could be meant by that claim?

00:12:52.450 --> 00:12:54.470
It's likely that the maker
of this pronouncement

00:12:54.470 --> 00:12:57.130
is certainly confident in his
belief that persons have souls

00:12:57.130 --> 00:12:59.993
and has extended the same
nature to his canid companion.

00:13:01.010 --> 00:13:03.850
Historically, what the soul
is has been changeable,

00:13:03.850 --> 00:13:07.540
spiritual, immaterial, essential,

00:13:07.540 --> 00:13:10.410
some component of mental experience.

00:13:10.410 --> 00:13:12.380
Without resolving this question,

00:13:12.380 --> 00:13:15.680
as my research with animals
addresses the fact of

00:13:15.680 --> 00:13:17.410
and content of mental experience,

00:13:17.410 --> 00:13:18.933
that's the part I'll focus on.

00:13:20.400 --> 00:13:22.360
And, as an animal researcher interested

00:13:22.360 --> 00:13:25.270
in making claims about
ability based on behavior,

00:13:25.270 --> 00:13:27.720
any prior attribution made to an animal

00:13:27.720 --> 00:13:29.700
is approached with caution,

00:13:29.700 --> 00:13:32.040
in an interest in deconstruction.

00:13:32.040 --> 00:13:34.200
What outward evidence is there

00:13:34.200 --> 00:13:37.840
of the existence or non-existence
of the thing attributed,

00:13:37.840 --> 00:13:39.940
the thing about the
animal to which we point

00:13:39.940 --> 00:13:42.020
as evidence of our claim.

00:13:42.020 --> 00:13:44.860
For instance, what behaviors
could induce people

00:13:44.860 --> 00:13:47.451
to believe that dogs have souls?

00:13:47.451 --> 00:13:50.573
Consider the case of Umka.

00:13:51.840 --> 00:13:53.643
Umka is a female Brussels griffin.

00:13:54.600 --> 00:13:57.911
Members of this breed, one
of the hundreds of breeds

00:13:57.911 --> 00:13:59.410
for which there is a national standard,

00:13:59.410 --> 00:14:02.880
restricting matings to maintain
a genetically ideal line,

00:14:02.880 --> 00:14:05.440
are expected to be under 10 lbs,

00:14:05.440 --> 00:14:08.743
and have faces with wide
set eyes, long eyelashes,

00:14:08.743 --> 00:14:11.263
a diminutive nose, and an underbite.

00:14:12.510 --> 00:14:13.910
These features are intended to,

00:14:13.910 --> 00:14:16.567
in the words of the American
Kennel Club standard,

00:14:16.567 --> 00:14:20.119
"Lend the dog an almost human expression."

00:14:20.119 --> 00:14:22.560
Although, note that according to the AKC,

00:14:22.560 --> 00:14:25.789
a wry mouth is a "serious fault".

00:14:25.789 --> 00:14:27.280
(audience laughs)

00:14:27.280 --> 00:14:29.960
In 2011, Umka was the subject of a lawsuit

00:14:29.960 --> 00:14:33.700
filed by her owner against
Raising Rover, LTD,

00:14:33.700 --> 00:14:37.113
a pet store which sold
Umka to her for $1600.00.

00:14:38.030 --> 00:14:40.080
Shortly after purchasing
Umka, her new owner

00:14:40.080 --> 00:14:42.080
became aware of various
serious health issues

00:14:42.080 --> 00:14:43.193
in the then puppy.

